parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to unexpected deployment, causing injuries or accidents, or failure to deploy in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag light on the odometer panel
failure to deploy airbags in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair can lead to continued exposure to safety risks, causing inconvenience, and potential harm to consumers.
symptoms: inability to sell or trade the vehicle due to open recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering control module can cause complete loss of power steering, leading to serious safety risks for all passengers and other drivers on the road. This failure can also communicate with other modules and systems, potentially causing errors and faults with the ABS and start/stop systems.
symptoms: Red steering wheel light on the dash
error codes populating on the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack can cause loss of power steering, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents and serious safety risks.
The failure of the electromechanical steering unit can cause the steering to lock, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents and serious safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Thermostat and Engine Temperature Control Actuator
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty thermostat and engine temperature control actuator can cause the engine to overheat, leading to potential engine damage, breakdowns, and safety risks.
Fuel pump failure can cause the engine to suddenly lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds.
The failure of the automatic engine shut-off system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to restart, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle requires multiple attempts to restart
the vehicle needs to be put in park and turned on/off to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress and Electrical System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the vehicle's electrical system can cause damage to critical components, leading to warning light illuminations, instrument panel failures, and safety risks.
symptoms: message indicating the vehicle is unsafe to drive is displayed
water damage to the computer system
failure of the computer image processing module and camera module.
